26|115| I am nothing but a plain warner.‚Äù
26|116| Said they: ‚ÄúIndeed, if thou desist not, O Noah, thou wilt surely be stoned to death!‚Äù
26|117| [Whereupon] he prayed: ‚ÄúO my Sustainer! Behold, my people have given me the lie:
26|118| hence, lay Thou wide open the truth between me and them, and save me and those of the believers who are with me!‚Äù
26|119| And so We saved him and those [who were] with him in the fully-laden ark,
26|120| and then We caused those who stayed behind to drown.
26|121| In this [story], behold, there is a message [unto men], even though most of them will not believe [in it].
26|122| But, verily, thy Sustainer - He alone - is almighty, a dispenser of grace
