26|152| those who spread corruption on earth instead of setting things to rights!‚Äù
26|153| Said they: ‚ÄúThou art but one of the bewitched!
26|154| Thou art nothing but a mortal like ourselves! Come, then, forward with a token [of thy mission] if thou art a man of truth!‚Äù
26|155| Replied he: ‚ÄúThis she-camel shall have a share of water, and you shall have a share of water, on the days appointed [therefor];
26|156| and do her no harm, lest suffering befall you on an awesome day!‚Äù
26|157| But they cruelly slaughtered her - and then they had cause to regret it:
26|158| for the suffering [predicted by Salih,] befell them [then and there]. In this [story], behold, there is a message [unto men], even though most of them will not believe [in it].
26|159| But, verily, thy Sustainer - He alone ‚Äì is almighty, a dispenser of grace!
26|160| [AND] the people of Lot gave the lie to [one of God‚Äôs] message-bearers
