54|21| for, how severe is the suffering which I inflict when My warnings are disregarded!
54|22| Hence, indeed, We made this Qur‚Äôan easy to bear in mind: who, then, is willing to take it to heart?
54|23| [AND the tribe of] Thamud gave the lie to all [Our] warnings;
54|24| and they said: ‚ÄúAre we to follow one single mortal, one from among ourselves? In that case, behold, we would certainly sink into error and folly!
54|25| Why - on him alone from among all of us should a [divine] reminder have been bestowed? Nay, but he is a boastful liar!‚Äù
54|26| [And God said:] ‚ÄúOn the morrow they will come to know who the boastful liar is!
